  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "1ce4750c-f3ba-8022-92ff-ec9b0fda3e54",
      "heading": "Summary Table KT",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Flaw of Previous Models",
          "Novelty of Model",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Inteligent Tutoring System",
          "Answering next question correctly",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "4151 learners in ASSISTments2009, 19840 learners in ASSISTments2015, 333 learners in Statics2011 and 4000 synthetic learners",
          "Each dataset refers to its own context",
          "Questions, \nLMS logs",
          "[Sequences of Answers]",
          "Current KT models consider the whole sequence of answers and not specifically the most recent answers. \n\nAll methods used the embedding of answers directly into the model.",
          "Authors introduce convolution to identify local interactions and patterns in the sequence of answers:\n\nThe vector is converted into a matrix.\n\nCNNs are used to reduce dimensionality and locally encode potential patterns.",
          "Sequence vectors are reshaped into a Matrix, which is given as argument to a Convolutional Layer, followed by an average pooling layer.\n\nThese are then given as iput to a LSTM.\n\n",
          "DKT, DKVMN, SKVMN, SAKT, CKT",
          "Holdout Method",
          "ASSISTments2009: {AUC: 0.8254 - CKT (k=4, b=80)}\n\nASSISTments2015: {AUC: 0.7291 - CKT (k=4, b=80)}\n\nStatics2011: {AUC: 0.8279 - DKT}\n\nSynthetic-5: {AUC: 0.8253 - MKVMN}",
          "Authors develop a new apporach at knowledge tracing. Models are followed by a set of optimization attempts. \n\nAuthors argue that this KT approach can help professors and learners track the learning progress of learners and check exercise realtionships.",
          "Model evaluation should use ranking instead of only showing performance results.\n\nMore metrics of evaluation should be considered. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
